1
00:00:04,546 --> 00:00:06,381
THE FOLLOWING CONTENT CONTAINS DEPICTIONS
OF DOMESTIC ABUSE.

2
00:00:06,465 --> 00:00:07,466
VIEWER DISCRETION IS ADVISED.

3
00:00:37,538 --> 00:00:40,457
Ah, shit. I really thought
you'd do better than this.

4
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:49,967
Why are you giving me this?

5
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:53,011
Sunok, I think I really like you.

6
00:00:53,095 --> 00:00:54,221
You like me?

7
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:55,305
Yeah.

8
00:00:59,309 --> 00:01:01,770
Hold on.

9
00:01:01,854 --> 00:01:03,605
Up next...

10
00:01:03,689 --> 00:01:05,649
Pretty sure it's my turn.

11
00:01:05,732 --> 00:01:07,359
And here's the ribbon!

12
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:08,527
Whoa!

13
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:10,821
In an effort
to boost areas hit hard by the decline

14
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:12,114
of the coal industry...

15
00:01:12,197 --> 00:01:13,532
Hey, where's Sunok?

16
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:14,950
- Mm, not sure.
- I don't know where she is.

17
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:16,159
GOLD LAND HOTEL &amp; RESORT CONSTRUCTION SITE

18
00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:17,744
- Sunok needs to see this.
- She must be somewhere.

19
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:33,093
What the...

20
00:01:33,177 --> 00:01:34,386
Shit!

21
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:35,470
This crazy bastard!

22
00:01:35,554 --> 00:01:36,722
Hold him, hold him!

23
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:38,390
- Fuck me.
- That way.

24
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:41,018
Come on.

25
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:43,437
Don't be so rash.
You're still young.

26
00:01:44,605 --> 00:01:47,065
What you should be doing is working
to pay off your debts.

27
00:01:48,275 --> 00:01:50,736
How could I ever pay it all back?

28
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:52,696
I know, right?

29
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,573
On your police salary?

30
00:01:55,407 --> 00:01:58,118
Well, you should've known your place
before pushing it so far.

31
00:01:58,202 --> 00:01:59,453
I know, I know.

32
00:02:00,037 --> 00:02:03,040
Just kill me,
and only me, okay?

33
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:05,667
But please leave
that innocent woman alone.

34
00:02:05,751 --> 00:02:07,002
I'm begging you.

35
00:02:07,628 --> 00:02:09,338
You don't need to pay us back.

36
00:02:10,172 --> 00:02:11,465
At least not entirely with money.

37
00:02:13,175 --> 00:02:14,635
Constable Kim Jinman.

38
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:17,471
What if...

39
00:02:20,182 --> 00:02:22,309
You became my man instead, yeah?

40
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:05,746
EPISODE 7
VILLAINS

41
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:21,720
Why are you here?

42
00:04:23,514 --> 00:04:24,848
H-Heeju.

43
00:04:27,476 --> 00:04:29,436
I told you not to come here, didn't I?

44
00:04:30,145 --> 00:04:32,231
- The gold bars aren't here.
- Let's not do this.

45
00:04:32,814 --> 00:04:35,859
Let's just take the gold
and leave together.

46
00:04:35,943 --> 00:04:37,694
I already made
the deal with the buyers.

47
00:04:37,778 --> 00:04:40,447
All we need to do is go to Cambodia
and show them the gold bars.

48
00:04:40,531 --> 00:04:42,533
We'll have 100 billion won in our account!

49
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:44,952
I'm already giving you half.

50
00:04:45,744 --> 00:04:47,162
Isn't that enough?

51
00:04:47,246 --> 00:04:49,581
-Do you really have to take it all?
-Heeju.

52
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:58,757
Heeju, what happened to you?

53
00:05:00,175 --> 00:05:01,802
Why are you doing this?

54
00:05:14,523 --> 00:05:16,024
So this is what it was like.

55
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:18,861
The place you grew up in.

56
00:05:21,113 --> 00:05:22,698
You said it was hell.

57
00:05:22,781 --> 00:05:24,283
So why are you here again?

58
00:05:25,576 --> 00:05:26,702
What happened to you?

59
00:05:30,581 --> 00:05:32,457
Look, if this is because
of something I've done...

60
00:05:34,168 --> 00:05:36,086
...at least give me a chance
to explain myself.

61
00:05:37,171 --> 00:05:39,548
You can do that, can't you?
After all we've been through?

62
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:42,342
Dokyung.

63
00:05:44,428 --> 00:05:45,637
Look at us right now.

64
00:05:48,223 --> 00:05:49,391
This is the reason.

65
00:05:49,975 --> 00:05:52,436
This is why we shouldn't
be together any longer.

66
00:05:54,188 --> 00:05:55,606
Nothing happened.

67
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:57,149
And we're not bad people.

68
00:05:58,275 --> 00:05:59,902
This is just how life is.

69
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:03,155
When you win something really big.

70
00:06:05,157 --> 00:06:06,909
You have to lose something else.

71
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:09,369
A thing that's less precious.

72
00:06:10,329 --> 00:06:11,496
And quite frankly...

73
00:06:12,664 --> 00:06:15,209
...I'm the one who has the gold now.
It's mine.

74
00:06:15,292 --> 00:06:17,711
It's up to me whether I share
it with you or not.

75
00:06:19,213 --> 00:06:20,214
Heeju.

76
00:06:22,174 --> 00:06:23,217
Get out.

77
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:26,303
And don't ever look for me again.

78
00:06:28,347 --> 00:06:29,973
It's true that because of you...

79
00:06:31,058 --> 00:06:33,560
...I finally got out of the hell hole
I'd been living in.

80
00:06:35,229 --> 00:06:36,980
And being with you made me happy.

81
00:06:38,315 --> 00:06:41,527
But we can't be happy together anymore.
That's why it needs to end.

82
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:32,160
-Thank you.
-Oh.

83
00:07:32,244 --> 00:07:33,370
Thank you very much.

84
00:07:39,126 --> 00:07:40,127
That's great to hear.

85
00:07:42,254 --> 00:07:44,006
-And so it begins.
-Ah, look who it is!

86
00:07:44,089 --> 00:07:45,841
Sir, you're here.

87
00:07:45,924 --> 00:07:48,343
- Mr. Ahn.
- Thank you for coming. I know you're busy.

88
00:07:48,427 --> 00:07:49,678
Well, how could I miss it?

89
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:51,388
It's your business, Mr. Ahn.

90
00:07:52,681 --> 00:07:54,683
Oh, right.
This is our partner from Cambodia.

91
00:07:54,766 --> 00:07:55,767
-Ah.
-Our governor.

92
00:07:55,851 --> 00:07:56,935
-How do you do?
-Nice to meet you.

93
00:07:57,019 --> 00:07:58,020
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

94
00:07:58,103 --> 00:07:59,688
- Of course.
- Yes.

95
00:07:59,771 --> 00:08:00,939
-Thank you.
-Thank you very much.

96
00:08:01,023 --> 00:08:01,982
- Thank you.
- It's been a pleasure.

97
00:08:02,065 --> 00:08:03,025
Absolutely.

98
00:08:03,108 --> 00:08:04,067
And this
is the congressman.

99
00:08:04,151 --> 00:08:05,777
I've been looking forward
to meeting you.

100
00:08:11,909 --> 00:08:13,869
The actors played their parts well.

101
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:16,914
Make sure everyone keeps their mouth shut.

102
00:08:16,997 --> 00:08:18,248
No loose lips.

103
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,835
And I want this deal on
the front page tomorrow.

104
00:08:21,919 --> 00:08:23,128
Understood, sir.

105
00:08:24,463 --> 00:08:25,881
Those Cambodians.

106
00:08:25,964 --> 00:08:28,050
Stick 'em in a room and keep 'em happy.

107
00:08:28,509 --> 00:08:30,552
Drugs, drinks, women, whatever it takes.

108
00:08:30,636 --> 00:08:31,970
Don't want 'em getting ideas.

109
00:08:32,054 --> 00:08:33,680
Yes, sir.

110
00:08:33,764 --> 00:08:36,308
Ah, all this bullshit
for one single casket!

111
00:08:37,184 --> 00:08:38,185
Hello, sir.

112
00:08:38,268 --> 00:08:39,269
It's been a while.

113
00:08:51,198 --> 00:08:52,950
Where's the casket?

114
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:54,034
Who took it?

115
00:08:55,285 --> 00:08:57,829
Yeah, well, it's, uh...

116
00:08:59,456 --> 00:09:00,457
It was this woman, right?

117
00:09:02,334 --> 00:09:03,585
- Yeah.
- It was?

118
00:09:03,669 --> 00:09:05,963
- Yeah.
- Look, different name.

119
00:09:06,588 --> 00:09:08,966
So it wasn't Cha Yujin.
It was Kim Heeju.

120
00:09:11,635 --> 00:09:13,512
The thing is, sir,
it's just...

121
00:09:14,263 --> 00:09:16,640
...we're talkin' about one ton
of gold bars, here.

122
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:18,475
And having to smuggle and sell it?

123
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:21,395
I don't think anyone could do
that by themselves.

124
00:09:22,354 --> 00:09:23,438
They must have had help.

125
00:09:23,522 --> 00:09:25,190
Someone else is pulling the strings?

126
00:09:26,817 --> 00:09:27,943
Suspect anyone?

127
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:29,278
We'll find out
once we investigate.

128
00:09:30,654 --> 00:09:35,534
Although, with the police being involved,
it can get pretty risky.

129
00:09:35,617 --> 00:09:36,702
Do you want cash?

130
00:09:36,785 --> 00:09:37,786
Well, I...

131
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:41,832
...I do always need more money, sir.

132
00:09:42,457 --> 00:09:43,876
How much you want?

133
00:09:44,793 --> 00:09:46,712
One gold bar.
That's it.

134
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:47,796
That's all I want.

135
00:09:49,047 --> 00:09:50,424
Give me a week to work on this.

136
00:09:51,675 --> 00:09:53,510
I'll find all 100 gold bars.

137
00:09:54,803 --> 00:09:56,305
Keep one for myself.

138
00:09:56,388 --> 00:10:00,517
And then I'll return
the other 99 back to you, sir.

139
00:10:01,018 --> 00:10:02,895
What do you plan to do with one gold bar?

140
00:10:02,978 --> 00:10:06,481
Well, uh, you know,
I'm getting old now.

141
00:10:07,774 --> 00:10:09,693
I'm thinking of quitting the force.

142
00:10:09,776 --> 00:10:11,612
I wanna buy a pawnshop.

143
00:10:11,695 --> 00:10:14,156
Sit back and take it easy.
Play loan shark.

144
00:10:14,656 --> 00:10:16,283
Just live like that.

145
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:19,912
I think I've done more than enough, sir.
That's a good end for me.

146
00:10:22,456 --> 00:10:25,125
Sure.

147
00:10:26,001 --> 00:10:28,086
Bring the casket back,
and I'll give you one.

148
00:10:30,631 --> 00:10:31,882
Thank you, sir.

149
00:10:34,051 --> 00:10:35,636
If you need to get in touch,

150
00:10:35,719 --> 00:10:37,304
-go through Chief Cheon.
-Yes.

151
00:10:39,264 --> 00:10:41,975
Well, then, we have an agreement.
Excuse me.

152
00:10:44,353 --> 00:10:45,687
- Hey, Kim Jinman.
- Yes, sir.

153
00:10:47,231 --> 00:10:50,567
You knew about the gold all along
and you didn't lose your cool.

154
00:10:51,652 --> 00:10:52,903
You were first, right?

155
00:10:53,195 --> 00:10:54,279
To find out about it?

156
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:56,740
You're the one who told Hocheol.

157
00:10:57,616 --> 00:10:58,659
But you never thought...

158
00:10:59,993 --> 00:11:02,454
"Should I just keep all the gold
and run away?"

159
00:11:02,538 --> 00:11:04,289
You never felt the urge
to do anything like that?

160
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:09,586
No, how could I?
I wouldn't touch your property, sir.

161
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:14,174
Right.

162
00:11:15,217 --> 00:11:17,135
You've always played it small,
haven't you?

163
00:11:18,762 --> 00:11:20,681
I once told him I'd take
his wife's kidney.

164
00:11:20,764 --> 00:11:23,475
He tried to hang himself.

165
00:11:23,559 --> 00:11:25,435
That's how freaked out he was.

166
00:11:26,144 --> 00:11:28,397
So I said I'd spare her life.

167
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:32,484
And this man starts grovelling, begging.
"I'll do anything you say!"

168
00:11:33,652 --> 00:11:35,153
Just crying.

169
00:11:37,406 --> 00:11:40,951
And that-that's why I like you,
Kim Jinman!

170
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:42,494
You're still useful!

171
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:51,128
Four five two one. No.

172
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:53,088
How about this one here?

173
00:11:53,172 --> 00:11:55,132
JANGGAK TRADE INC.

174
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:56,550
That's not it, either.

175
00:11:57,342 --> 00:11:59,511
Four three two oh.
Four three two oh.

176
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:07,477
Ah, shit.
What is it now?

177
00:12:10,439 --> 00:12:11,607
Yeah, what is it?

178
00:12:11,690 --> 00:12:14,610
Are you looking for
a five two seven nine Santa Fe?

179
00:12:14,693 --> 00:12:15,694
Yes.

180
00:12:16,403 --> 00:12:18,488
I'm here, fucker. Here.

181
00:12:18,572 --> 00:12:19,990
Shit.

182
00:12:24,995 --> 00:12:27,748
Hey. I checked all
the cars here earlier today.

183
00:12:28,415 --> 00:12:29,416
It's not here.

184
00:12:31,168 --> 00:12:33,212
So then Park made you do this?

185
00:12:33,295 --> 00:12:35,339
No, Chairman Ahn.

186
00:12:36,632 --> 00:12:38,300
Fuck, this is driving me crazy.

187
00:12:41,136 --> 00:12:42,679
Hey, what's with that car, anyways?

188
00:12:43,263 --> 00:12:44,264
Is it Cha Yujin's?

189
00:12:44,765 --> 00:12:46,016
Well, I don't know.

190
00:12:49,311 --> 00:12:50,312
Hey.

191
00:12:51,563 --> 00:12:52,564
Thought you said you were done.

192
00:12:52,648 --> 00:12:55,234
You weren't gonna work for Geumseong,
so why are you?

193
00:12:55,901 --> 00:12:57,110
We lost Lee Dokyung.

194
00:12:59,738 --> 00:13:00,739
Gosh.

195
00:13:00,822 --> 00:13:02,866
The department's already giving me hell
for this.

196
00:13:03,242 --> 00:13:04,451
Now the director, too.

197
00:13:08,997 --> 00:13:10,832
Just call it a night for now, yeah?

198
00:13:11,875 --> 00:13:15,212
My best guess is that there's a good
chance they got rid of it already.

199
00:13:15,295 --> 00:13:17,297
Probably dumped it in
a reservoir or something.

200
00:13:18,757 --> 00:13:22,094
Just tell Park that the car belonged
to Janggak Trading.

201
00:13:23,262 --> 00:13:25,097
Right.
Yeah, that's a good call.

202
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:26,181
Yeah.

203
00:13:37,609 --> 00:13:38,610
You find it yet?

204
00:13:39,319 --> 00:13:41,238
Uh, no.
No, not exactly.

205
00:13:46,618 --> 00:13:48,287
You're a stupid fuck.
You know that?

206
00:13:52,416 --> 00:13:55,586
Now wait. You see,
it's not a private vehicle.

207
00:13:55,669 --> 00:13:57,129
It belongs to a company.

208
00:13:57,963 --> 00:13:59,173
Fuck, which one?

209
00:13:59,631 --> 00:14:00,883
It's called Janggak Trading.

210
00:14:01,592 --> 00:14:03,427
It looks like a trading company,

211
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:05,554
but they buy cheap Chinese cars
and sell them overseas.

212
00:14:06,305 --> 00:14:07,472
Heo Donggu's company?

213
00:14:08,265 --> 00:14:09,892
Yeah.
Do you know it?

214
00:14:11,894 --> 00:14:12,936
Good work.

215
00:14:20,736 --> 00:14:22,112
It's because my dad
suddenly collapsed.

216
00:14:22,196 --> 00:14:23,197
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

217
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:26,575
I need to leave so I can help
him out on his farm.

218
00:14:27,117 --> 00:14:28,243
You're an orphan.

219
00:14:28,327 --> 00:14:29,536
Uh...

220
00:14:31,205 --> 00:14:32,956
...he's actually my uncle, not my dad.

221
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:36,293
Do you think we're a real company
'cause we pay you a salary?

222
00:14:36,376 --> 00:14:38,504
You've always been able
to walk in as you please.

223
00:14:39,171 --> 00:14:41,465
I'll cut off your ear
if you wanna walk out, though.

224
00:14:42,883 --> 00:14:45,177
-Yes, I understand.
-You understand?

225
00:14:46,178 --> 00:14:47,513
Seriously?

226
00:14:47,596 --> 00:14:49,848
Just think it over.

227
00:14:49,932 --> 00:14:52,059
You won't make this kind
of money anywhere else.

228
00:14:52,142 --> 00:14:54,019
And you're one of our best.

229
00:14:56,605 --> 00:14:58,649
Now get out.
Go on.

230
00:14:58,732 --> 00:15:01,401
Back to work, now!
Go, go, go, go.

231
00:15:05,155 --> 00:15:06,156
Hey.

232
00:15:11,119 --> 00:15:12,120
Sir.

233
00:15:15,415 --> 00:15:16,750
It was you.

234
00:15:20,921 --> 00:15:21,922
No, it wasn't!

235
00:15:24,132 --> 00:15:25,342
What do you mean?

236
00:15:27,469 --> 00:15:30,055
You're that kid whose ear
I almost took off, right?

237
00:15:31,807 --> 00:15:34,184
Uh, yes. That's correct.

238
00:15:35,853 --> 00:15:36,937
It's still on there.

239
00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:39,523
Yes. It healed up well.

240
00:15:44,152 --> 00:15:45,279
Go on.

241
00:15:54,538 --> 00:15:55,581
Boss.

242
00:15:56,206 --> 00:15:57,499
Have a seat over here.

243
00:15:57,583 --> 00:15:59,168
Or should I call you President?

244
00:15:59,251 --> 00:16:01,044
You think I dragged myself here...

245
00:16:02,296 --> 00:16:04,006
...just so I can sit in that chair again?

246
00:16:04,089 --> 00:16:07,426
That's true.

247
00:16:09,469 --> 00:16:11,013
Gitae, let's find the casket.

248
00:16:11,555 --> 00:16:13,056
Do you even know where it is?

249
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:16,643
Well, come on, then!

250
00:16:16,727 --> 00:16:18,187
Let's go get it!

251
00:16:18,270 --> 00:16:20,939
And then, boom, your honor is back!

252
00:16:21,565 --> 00:16:22,691
We have to!

253
00:16:30,324 --> 00:16:31,783
It's Detective Kim.

254
00:16:31,867 --> 00:16:33,994
He thinks Janggak Trading is behind this.

255
00:16:34,786 --> 00:16:36,330
Janggak Trading?

256
00:16:36,413 --> 00:16:39,333
He told me you'd recognize
what that refers to.

257
00:16:46,590 --> 00:16:47,716
What's Janggak Trading?

258
00:16:48,467 --> 00:16:52,262
Oh, hello, sir.
Uh, it's Heo Donggu's company. Yeah.

259
00:16:52,346 --> 00:16:55,224
He was the man you kicked out, uh,
about ten years ago.

260
00:16:55,516 --> 00:16:57,726
- Oh.
- You remember, right?

261
00:16:57,809 --> 00:16:59,645
Okay, stay there.
Keep an eye on him.

262
00:17:06,068 --> 00:17:08,904
Grab a few guys.
Head to Janggak Trading.

263
00:17:09,112 --> 00:17:10,113
When you get there,

264
00:17:10,197 --> 00:17:13,534
cut off Heo Donggu's other ear
and find the casket. Get moving.

265
00:17:14,201 --> 00:17:15,661
Yes, sir.

266
00:17:15,744 --> 00:17:17,788
Ah, let's go.

267
00:17:17,871 --> 00:17:19,164
Janggak Trading?

268
00:17:19,873 --> 00:17:20,874
Mm-hmm.

269
00:17:22,125 --> 00:17:23,710
You know what those guys do, right?

270
00:17:23,794 --> 00:17:25,128
And you're buying a ferry ticket there?

271
00:17:25,212 --> 00:17:26,505
I know.

272
00:17:27,256 --> 00:17:28,423
I got the car there.

273
00:17:30,884 --> 00:17:32,553
And that's where I got the bullets, too.

274
00:17:33,428 --> 00:17:36,306
Ah, just give half the gold bars
to Dokyung and let him figure it out!

275
00:17:36,974 --> 00:17:39,601
That bastard is an expert at smuggling!
He'll know what to do!

276
00:17:43,230 --> 00:17:46,191
