509
00:34:17,850 --> 00:34:19,893
Ah, dammit.

510
00:34:46,170 --> 00:34:50,799
VEHICLE TRANSFER CERTIFICATE
JU HARAN

511
00:34:50,883 --> 00:34:52,009
Ju Haran.

512
00:34:52,092 --> 00:34:54,553
I've heard that name before.
Fuck.

513
00:34:56,430 --> 00:34:57,639
Dammit.

514
00:35:02,895 --> 00:35:04,688
That's the bitch I killed.

515
00:35:12,529 --> 00:35:19,536
YES MONEY

516
00:35:36,053 --> 00:35:38,388
Boss.

517
00:35:38,472 --> 00:35:40,015
- Boss.
- What?

518
00:35:40,098 --> 00:35:42,017
Did you see a ghost or something?

519
00:35:46,897 --> 00:35:47,981
Sir, what're...

520
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:52,319
Nobody saw anything,
so keep your mouth shut.

521
00:35:53,570 --> 00:35:55,155
And no makin' any phone calls!

522
00:35:55,239 --> 00:35:56,698
- Yes, sir.
- Now get the fuck out.

523
00:35:56,782 --> 00:35:57,866
Shut the door.

524
00:35:58,867 --> 00:36:00,577
Why'd you come here?

525
00:36:03,372 --> 00:36:04,581
You know you're being hunted.

526
00:36:04,665 --> 00:36:07,000
The Geumseong guys
are all over looking for you.

527
00:36:08,836 --> 00:36:10,170
Where else should I go?

528
00:36:11,213 --> 00:36:12,506
This here is my turf.

529
00:36:13,382 --> 00:36:14,925
You know Chief Cheon died, right?

530
00:36:15,384 --> 00:36:16,468
He was cremated.

531
00:36:17,177 --> 00:36:19,012
-Yeah?
-Leave Jeongsan.

532
00:36:19,763 --> 00:36:21,723
Chairman Ahn will find out you were here.

533
00:36:21,807 --> 00:36:23,350
And then he'll murder us both.

534
00:36:25,644 --> 00:36:26,895
Where's Ju Haran?

535
00:36:29,481 --> 00:36:30,482
I don't know.

536
00:36:32,234 --> 00:36:34,027
The Geumseong guys must be looking
for her.

537
00:36:35,404 --> 00:36:36,405
Gitae.

538
00:36:38,740 --> 00:36:40,534
Do you know who Ju Haran is?

539
00:36:41,952 --> 00:36:42,995
No, who?

540
00:36:43,495 --> 00:36:44,830
You know Gu Jaok, right?

541
00:36:45,664 --> 00:36:47,791
She's the largest backer in Gangwon.

542
00:36:49,084 --> 00:36:52,713
There's no one in Jeongsan who hasn't
set foot on land that old lady owns.

543
00:36:53,547 --> 00:36:55,632
Ju Haran is her granddaughter.

544
00:36:55,716 --> 00:36:56,717
What?

545
00:36:57,551 --> 00:36:58,719
Around a year ago...

546
00:36:59,678 --> 00:37:03,599
...Chairman Ahn wanted to buy the 2%
of Gu's stake in Gold Land.

547
00:37:05,434 --> 00:37:08,395
That would have made him Gold Land's
biggest shareholder.

548
00:37:08,896 --> 00:37:10,856
However, Ms. Gu knew what he was doing...

549
00:37:12,274 --> 00:37:14,318
...and she refused to hand over her stake.

550
00:37:15,068 --> 00:37:17,571
So I found her collateral,
and took it from her.

551
00:37:19,156 --> 00:37:20,157
Ju Haran.

552
00:37:20,991 --> 00:37:22,618
So what's going on?

553
00:37:23,118 --> 00:37:27,789
If Ju is her granddaughter,
she took the casket...

554
00:37:28,916 --> 00:37:31,084
...is Ms. Gu the one behind all this?

555
00:37:31,168 --> 00:37:33,128
No, that's not it.

556
00:37:35,380 --> 00:37:36,840
Ju Haran's already dead.

557
00:37:37,841 --> 00:37:39,009
I killed her.

558
00:37:40,010 --> 00:37:42,804
Mr. Jin took care of the body
and dumped it at the farm.

559
00:37:43,472 --> 00:37:46,475
Well then, who's the Ju Haran
with the casket now?

560
00:37:46,558 --> 00:37:48,185
She's a fake.

561
00:37:48,268 --> 00:37:50,020
Someone's pretending
to be Ju Haran,

562
00:37:50,103 --> 00:37:51,772
and they've even been using her ID.

563
00:37:53,023 --> 00:37:54,483
But as you probably know...

564
00:37:55,776 --> 00:37:57,986
...we're supposed to keep hold
of every ID card.

565
00:38:01,156 --> 00:38:03,909
That's right. ID card.

566
00:38:06,870 --> 00:38:07,871
Let's see.

567
00:38:07,955 --> 00:38:09,331
Fuck.

568
00:38:09,414 --> 00:38:10,749
Where is it?

569
00:38:22,970 --> 00:38:23,971
What's this?

570
00:38:27,099 --> 00:38:28,976
Her ID card is missing.

571
00:38:32,813 --> 00:38:34,898
I didn't do it!

572
00:38:35,774 --> 00:38:36,984
Then who was it?

573
00:38:37,818 --> 00:38:39,027
Who has access to them?

574
00:38:42,781 --> 00:38:44,032
Someone with access.

575
00:38:44,116 --> 00:38:45,367
Who's here alone.

576
00:38:46,159 --> 00:38:47,160
Woogy.

577
00:38:47,995 --> 00:38:50,372
That fucking punk that handles
the office supplies and the cleaning,

578
00:38:50,455 --> 00:38:51,748
all that stuff.

579
00:38:51,832 --> 00:38:53,500
Where's that bastard now?

580
00:38:53,584 --> 00:38:55,586
He tried to leave the company recently.

581
00:38:56,461 --> 00:38:57,629
That piece of shit.

582
00:38:59,089 --> 00:39:00,132
Hey, Moonsu!

583
00:39:01,008 --> 00:39:02,926
- Yes, Boss?
- You work with Woogy, right?

584
00:39:03,177 --> 00:39:04,178
Yes.

585
00:39:04,261 --> 00:39:06,763
Go find him!
Find him and bring him here!

586
00:39:06,847 --> 00:39:08,223
But Woogy already quit.

587
00:39:08,724 --> 00:39:10,017
Yeah, no shit, you dumb ass!

588
00:39:10,100 --> 00:39:11,977
So fucking bring him to me right now!

589
00:39:12,311 --> 00:39:13,312
Yes, right away.

590
00:39:18,358 --> 00:39:21,069
So, what are you gonna do now, Boss?

591
00:39:21,153 --> 00:39:22,404
What about you?

592
00:39:22,487 --> 00:39:23,906
What are you gonna do?

593
00:39:25,240 --> 00:39:27,075
I'm already tracking down
the fake Ju Haran

594
00:39:27,159 --> 00:39:28,493
and I'm close to finding her.

595
00:39:30,204 --> 00:39:33,248
You can go get that thief
who stole her ID card from us.

596
00:39:33,332 --> 00:39:35,250
After that, we find the casket.

597
00:39:35,709 --> 00:39:36,710
So then...

598
00:39:37,294 --> 00:39:41,131
Wait a sec. Find the casket.
I know that's what you want.

599
00:39:42,007 --> 00:39:44,301
But we'll need to double cross Geumseong
for it.

600
00:39:45,135 --> 00:39:46,887
Do you really think that's worth it?

601
00:39:49,139 --> 00:39:50,933
You don't even know what's inside of it,
do you?

602
00:39:51,016 --> 00:39:52,726
Obviously drugs!

603
00:39:52,809 --> 00:39:54,811
They're a pain in the ass to sell,
ya know?

604
00:39:55,312 --> 00:39:56,939
Gold bars.

605
00:39:58,524 --> 00:39:59,733
One ton.

606
00:40:01,318 --> 00:40:03,529
It's worth 150 billion won.

607
00:40:09,117 --> 00:40:11,495
Now do you get why I turned against Ahn?

608
00:40:16,083 --> 00:40:17,084
But...

609
00:40:19,002 --> 00:40:22,506
...if it's that kind of money,
Chairman Ahn's not just gonna give up.

610
00:40:23,382 --> 00:40:26,802
If he loses that casket,
he'll end up in one of his own.

611
00:40:26,885 --> 00:40:28,846
That's the investment money
from Cambodia

612
00:40:28,929 --> 00:40:30,722
for the joint Gold Resort development.

613
00:40:31,473 --> 00:40:35,060
If the deal falls through
and they don't get their principal back...

614
00:40:37,229 --> 00:40:38,856
...they're not just gonna
let him walk away.

615
00:40:40,607 --> 00:40:42,234
Now, you need to decide.

616
00:40:45,404 --> 00:40:46,947
Whose side are you on?

617
00:40:50,033 --> 00:40:51,493
'Cause I'm all in.

618
00:41:20,189 --> 00:41:21,273
You're here.

619
00:41:21,356 --> 00:41:22,482
Yeah.

620
00:41:26,486 --> 00:41:28,113
That a side effect of the chemo?

621
00:41:29,489 --> 00:41:31,450
Well, at least
you're getting treatment.

622
00:41:31,533 --> 00:41:32,701
You'll be good soon.

623
00:41:35,537 --> 00:41:36,914
Tomorrow's my surgery.

624
00:41:37,873 --> 00:41:39,708
Really? That's good to hear.

625
00:41:40,626 --> 00:41:41,793
I hope it goes well.

626
00:41:43,128 --> 00:41:44,379
Better sooner than later.

627
00:41:48,175 --> 00:41:49,426
Will your niece be here?

628
00:41:49,510 --> 00:41:50,511
No.

629
00:41:54,348 --> 00:41:56,350
I called because I wanted
to see your face.

630
00:41:58,519 --> 00:42:00,604
Might be the last time I see you.

631
00:42:01,230 --> 00:42:03,899
What are you talking about?
Come on.

632
00:42:04,900 --> 00:42:05,901
Don't know.

633
00:42:08,654 --> 00:42:10,113
I just have a feeling it might.

634
00:42:10,822 --> 00:42:12,282
You're talking nonsense now.

635
00:42:12,908 --> 00:42:13,992
Jeez.

636
00:42:16,453 --> 00:42:17,579
Could...

637
00:42:18,997 --> 00:42:21,416
Could you give me a bath tonight?

638
00:42:22,209 --> 00:42:23,377
A bath?

639
00:42:24,253 --> 00:42:25,254
Mm-hmm.

640
00:42:27,172 --> 00:42:28,382
You remember...

641
00:42:30,592 --> 00:42:32,845
...when we were young
and I'd come home drunk...

642
00:42:33,470 --> 00:42:34,888
...you would help wash me up?

643
00:42:38,392 --> 00:42:39,768
I did?

644
00:42:40,727 --> 00:42:41,979
If I'm going to die...

645
00:42:44,356 --> 00:42:46,358
...I wanna die with some grace.

646
00:42:55,033 --> 00:42:56,118
Looking back...

647
00:42:57,870 --> 00:43:00,122
...that really was the spring time
of my life.

648
00:43:03,333 --> 00:43:04,585
Living in Namju.

649
00:43:07,588 --> 00:43:08,714
With you.

650
00:43:08,797 --> 00:43:10,924
The two of us in that little mining town.

651
00:43:14,595 --> 00:43:15,596
Yeah.

652
00:43:16,930 --> 00:43:18,640
I barely remember those days.

653
00:43:23,770 --> 00:43:25,606
I resented you afterward.

654
00:43:26,815 --> 00:43:27,900
For quite a while.

655
00:43:31,695 --> 00:43:34,489
I always wished that you
hadn't disappeared so suddenly.

656
00:43:37,117 --> 00:43:38,452
Even if I stayed...

657
00:43:43,665 --> 00:43:45,125
Fucking hell.

658
00:43:45,209 --> 00:43:46,502
What kind of a man were you with?

659
00:43:46,585 --> 00:43:47,586
Fuck.

660
00:43:49,630 --> 00:43:52,758
That's what happens when you're nothing
but bad luck.

661
00:43:54,801 --> 00:43:55,886
But back then...

662
00:43:56,803 --> 00:43:58,805
...it really was all I could do
to survive.

663
00:44:01,517 --> 00:44:03,602
The years I spent living with that man...

664
00:44:06,146 --> 00:44:07,606
...they were nothing but hell.

665
00:44:10,901 --> 00:44:13,487
It felt like it wouldn't end until one
of us died.

666
00:44:14,988 --> 00:44:16,031
But...

667
00:44:17,616 --> 00:44:19,326
...the thought of being
the first to die...

668
00:44:23,288 --> 00:44:24,581
...that seemed too unfair.

669
00:44:27,835 --> 00:44:28,836
So then...

670
00:44:29,628 --> 00:44:30,796
...I killed him.

671
00:44:33,882 --> 00:44:36,343
Han Cheoljung, that bastard.

672
00:44:38,804 --> 00:44:40,055
I killed him.

673
00:45:19,678 --> 00:45:21,096
I'll cut it now.

674
00:45:32,191 --> 00:45:34,568
You have a nice head shape.
Don't worry.

675
00:45:35,652 --> 00:45:38,864
There was that bald singer from the UK.
You used to like her, didn't you?

676
00:45:38,947 --> 00:45:41,575
You kind of look like her.
You look pretty.

677
00:45:41,658 --> 00:45:42,826
Not bad, right?

678
00:45:55,422 --> 00:45:56,965
Heeju isn't my niece.

679
00:45:59,092 --> 00:46:00,552
She's my daughter.

680
00:46:00,636 --> 00:46:01,637
What?

681
00:46:06,600 --> 00:46:08,060
And you're her father.

682
00:46:10,020 --> 00:46:11,271
After you left...

683
00:46:12,147 --> 00:46:14,274
...I found out that I was pregnant.

684
00:46:16,735 --> 00:46:18,987
The house where we lived together
in Namju...

685
00:46:20,489 --> 00:46:21,907
...that's where Heeju was born.

686
00:46:26,119 --> 00:46:27,913
You're kidding, right?

687
00:46:28,539 --> 00:46:29,540
It's a joke.

688
00:46:31,166 --> 00:46:32,417
That doesn't make any sense.

689
00:46:33,252 --> 00:46:35,671
I was going to keep it
a secret until I died.

690
00:46:36,839 --> 00:46:39,049
I didn't think I'd see you again.

691
00:46:39,883 --> 00:46:40,968
Okay, then.

692
00:46:41,051 --> 00:46:42,344
Why say all of this now?

693
00:46:43,971 --> 00:46:44,972
Jinman.

694
00:46:51,061 --> 00:46:52,062
Heeju...

695
00:46:53,188 --> 00:46:56,024
I think she's unhappy nowadays.

696
00:46:57,609 --> 00:46:59,152
She's in trouble.

697
00:47:00,696 --> 00:47:02,155
And it's all because of me, I know.

698
00:47:03,532 --> 00:47:06,201
I just can't be buried with all
of that guilt.

699
00:47:06,952 --> 00:47:09,121
Not when it was me
who made her that way.

700
00:47:10,163 --> 00:47:12,374
I've always told her she
was a luckless brat...

701
00:47:13,500 --> 00:47:15,335
...born from a luckless bitch.

702
00:47:17,629 --> 00:47:18,630
So could you...

703
00:47:19,673 --> 00:47:21,300
...could you please take care of her?

704
00:47:23,302 --> 00:47:25,512
Don't let her ruin
her life any further.

705
00:47:25,846 --> 00:47:28,432
Keep her out of prison
and safe from bad men.

706
00:47:29,892 --> 00:47:31,393
You're a police officer.

707
00:47:31,977 --> 00:47:33,020
And her dad.

708
00:47:33,604 --> 00:47:36,690
- So you need to protect your daughter now.
- Enough.

709
00:47:38,275 --> 00:47:39,443
Hey.

710
00:47:40,861 --> 00:47:43,447
Listen, I just have to ask,
how am I supposed to believe you?

711
00:47:43,906 --> 00:47:44,907
Huh?

712
00:47:45,699 --> 00:47:48,952
You were a working girl.
A lady of the night.

713
00:47:49,036 --> 00:47:50,287
What?

714
00:47:51,705 --> 00:47:53,290
You mean when I was a hostess?

715
00:47:53,999 --> 00:47:55,000
Yeah.

716
00:47:55,292 --> 00:47:56,293
I mean...

717
00:47:57,044 --> 00:47:59,463
...seriously, how the fuck would
I know whose daughter she is?

718
00:48:00,047 --> 00:48:01,048
I wouldn't.

719
00:48:01,131 --> 00:48:02,216
I do, though.

720
00:48:03,884 --> 00:48:05,511
You were the only one I was with then.

721
00:48:10,724 --> 00:48:13,435
Shit, this is really fucked.

722
00:48:22,319 --> 00:48:23,987
Shit.

723
00:48:29,910 --> 00:48:34,039
Hey. Have you told her, you know, that-

724
00:48:34,122 --> 00:48:35,707
that I'm, uh-I'm her dad?

725
00:48:35,791 --> 00:48:37,584
Or, does she know?

726
00:48:38,544 --> 00:48:39,586
I haven't.

727
00:48:41,171 --> 00:48:43,006
Heeju believes her father's dead.

728
00:48:45,801 --> 00:48:49,847
Would you tell your daughter
that her father was a gambling addict...

729
00:48:50,806 --> 00:48:52,766
...who ran off and abandoned her?

730
00:48:53,433 --> 00:48:54,977
That's good, then, yeah?

731
00:48:55,561 --> 00:48:57,312
Just keep it that way, okay?

732
00:48:58,105 --> 00:49:00,190
'Cause I-
I'm not her father.

733
00:49:00,274 --> 00:49:02,359
Got it?
Don't tell her.

734
00:49:03,068 --> 00:49:05,946
If you tell her I'm her father,
or anything like that,

735
00:49:06,029 --> 00:49:09,491
you, me, and her,
we're all gonna be fucked.

736
00:49:11,493 --> 00:49:13,245
The three of us will die.

737
00:49:13,328 --> 00:49:14,329
Understand?

738
00:49:15,497 --> 00:49:17,499
So stop saying nonsense.

739
00:49:18,417 --> 00:49:19,585
Seriously.

740
00:50:50,259 --> 00:50:52,928
Mokcheon Port, 9:00 p.m. tomorrow.

741
00:50:55,389 --> 00:50:56,431
See you there.

742
00:51:16,118 --> 00:51:18,453
INCOMING CALL
AUNTIE MIJA

743
00:51:20,414 --> 00:51:21,874
Hey, Auntie.

744
00:51:22,374 --> 00:51:23,667
Hey.

745
00:51:23,750 --> 00:51:25,127
Are you coming today?

746
00:51:27,045 --> 00:51:28,589
Why aren't you saying anything?

747
00:51:29,840 --> 00:51:32,885
You should be here.
Your mom might be dying.

748
00:51:33,468 --> 00:51:35,637
Ah, I just have a bad feeling.

749
00:51:35,721 --> 00:51:37,389
I really think you should come.

750
00:51:39,474 --> 00:51:40,559
Okay.

751
00:51:51,653 --> 00:51:52,779
Sunok.

752
00:51:53,280 --> 00:51:54,948
Everything will be all right.

753
00:51:55,657 --> 00:51:57,993
Just stay calm. Okay?

754
00:51:58,785 --> 00:51:59,786
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

755
00:51:59,870 --> 00:52:02,164
Oh, and Heeju will be here soon.

756
00:52:02,831 --> 00:52:03,874
See you later!

757
00:52:13,592 --> 00:52:19,264
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

758
00:52:20,307 --> 00:52:21,767
Is it over already?

759
00:52:21,850 --> 00:52:22,851
Yeah.

760
00:52:24,811 --> 00:52:26,605
They closed her up right away.

761
00:52:28,857 --> 00:52:31,276
I spoke with the doctor
before I called you.

762
00:52:32,069 --> 00:52:34,696
They said from here on out,
chemo won't help her.

763
00:52:36,698 --> 00:52:38,325
So she should go home.

764
00:52:38,784 --> 00:52:40,994
And spend the rest
of her time with family.

765
00:52:43,247 --> 00:52:44,540
Where are you right now?

766
00:52:45,624 --> 00:52:47,209
Why aren't you over here?

767
00:53:18,323 --> 00:53:19,783
Hi, Mom.

768
00:53:30,460 --> 00:53:33,589
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL
EMERGENCY CENTER
